  <brief_title>Safety Study of Elvucitabine in HIV-1 Subjects</brief_title>
  <official_title>14-Day Randomized Double-Blind Comparative Viral Kinetic Study of Elvucitabine Versus Lamivudine Once Daily to HIv-1 Subjects With M184V</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Thomas Jefferson University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Thomas Jefferson University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this 28 day study is to assess the viral kinetics and safety of elvucitabine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a 14 day on treat/14 day off treatment randomized, double blind viral kinetic study
      of elvucitabine versus lamivudine administered once daily to HIV infected subjects with a
      documented M184V variant.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
